<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b/82: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Portuguese Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Alte</hi></persName>)<note n="79b" xml:id="d269fn79b">At Bar
                                Harbor, Maine.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department informed British Minister at Lisbon is opposing applications
                            of Western Union Telegraph Company and Commercial <pb facs="0474" n="360" xml:id="pg_360"/> Cable Company for concessions to land and
                            operate cables at Azores.</p>
                        <p>This Government is deeply interested in having favorable and prompt
                            action taken on applications of American companies and would appreciate
                            any action you can take to that end.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>